itemDescription: English fighter with the YPJ (Kurdish Women's Protection Units)

wikipedia_page.main: Kimberley Taylor (born 1989), also known as Zilan Dilmar, is an English fighter with the Kurdish Women's Protection Units (YPJ) and the first British woman to join a female militia in Syria. She is a member of the YPJ's combat media team and was present at the Battle of Raqqa in 2017.
